												<BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Rytan_the_Wyrmlord wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>Actually, the statement I made was directly in reference to game pad controllers that have built in button sequencing.&nbsp; I'm not sure where everyone got the idea that I said macroing was ok, as it certainly is not.<BR>
<HR>

<P>Ummm, button sequencing IS macroing.&nbsp; It think the type of macroing you are referring to that is not allowed is having more sophisticated software that allows automatic <U><STRONG>UNATTENDED</STRONG></U> gameplay.&nbsp; Having a gamepad that twists songs while you chat, or fires the archery button for you every half-second while fighting is OK as I understand it.&nbsp; Having a macro program that auto-kites mobs for you by twisting songs while you watch TV downstairts, or a program that tradeskills for you while you go to the movies is against the EULA.</P>
<P>Please correct me if I am wrong.</P></BLOCKQUOTE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
