			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>Rytan-</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>What's the real difference between 3rd party software that sets a sequence of button-pushes and 3rd party software that sets a sequence of legitimate EQ commands?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The net effect of what we want is the same:&nbsp; The ability to be sociable with our friends online without sacrificing our effectiveness as players.&nbsp; Ever tried to talk while you twist?&nbsp; It's funny, for about 3 minutes.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>the conversation</DIV>
<DIV>goes something</DIV>
<DIV>like this for</DIV>
<DIV>us while we are</DIV>
<DIV>trying to twist</DIV>
<DIV>unless we</DIV>
<DIV>miss a key-</DIV>
<DIV>stroke in which</DIV>
<DIV>case we get</DIV>
<DIV>lines like44444444</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Lord forbid you try to keep your character behind a mob, meleeing it, while trying to 4-song twist and tell your group why playing manasong during a fight isn't such a great idea while at the same time trying to smooth over some guild drama. (I have done exactly that)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This game's fun should not be a function of our ability to enter casting commands every 3 seconds while constantly adjusting our position.&nbsp; Must we&nbsp;twist manually&nbsp;in order to meet the standards of the vision?</DIV>
																																		<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 100; overflow: hidden;">
														<p>Impressario Feroce of <br>Molto Espressivo, the All-Bard Guild on<br>Firiona Vie
